# 🍽️ RESTAURANT MANAGEMENT SYSTEM

## Project Report

---

## 1. Introduction

The Restaurant Management System is a console-based application developed using Python to simulate real-world restaurant operations. The primary objective of this project is to implement and demonstrate various data structures in a practical and meaningful way.

This system helps manage customer details, orders, billing, and menu organization efficiently. It provides a structured approach to handling restaurant workflows using fundamental data structures such as linked lists, stacks, queues, trees, and hash maps.

---

## 2. Objectives

* To design a system that manages restaurant operations efficiently
* To implement core data structures in real-world applications
* To improve understanding of data organization and processing
* To simulate order handling, billing, and customer management

---

## 3. System Overview

The system provides functionalities such as:

* Customer registration and management
* Order creation and tracking
* Kitchen order processing
* Bill generation
* Menu display and search
* Statistical analysis

It is a menu-driven program where users can interact through simple input commands.

---

## 4. Data Structures Used

### 4.1 Linked List

Used to store customer order history. Each node represents an order and allows efficient insertion and traversal.

### 4.2 Stack

Used for managing recent bills. It follows the Last-In-First-Out (LIFO) principle.

### 4.3 Queue

Used for processing kitchen orders in First-In-First-Out (FIFO) order.

### 4.4 Priority Queue

Used for handling VIP customers. Higher priority customers are served first.

### 4.5 Tree

Used to organize the restaurant menu into categories such as appetizers, main course, and beverages.

### 4.6 Hash Map

Used to store and retrieve customer details efficiently using phone numbers as keys.

### 4.7 Array

Used to track statistics such as hourly orders and popular items.

---

## 5. System Design

### 5.1 Modules

* Customer Module
* Order Management Module
* Billing Module
* Menu Management Module
* Statistics Module

### 5.2 Workflow

1. Customer registers or logs in
2. Customer places an order
3. Order is added to queue (VIP or regular)
4. Kitchen processes the order
5. Order is completed and bill is generated
6. Data is stored for future analysis

